				<outline text="Macs to HDTV via HDMI?" created="Sat, 01 Nov 2008 18:45:33 GMT">
					<outline text="Getting ready for election night when I'm going to have a few friends over to watch the returns, and either celebrate or..." created="Sat, 01 Nov 2008 18:45:40 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I have two Macs hooked up to HDTVs, one a Samsung the other a Sony Bravia, and until recently they had been connected via VGA. I was barely aware you could do it any other way. I thought the picture was great until I hooked up a Toshiba HDTV to the second video display on my G5 tower and the picture so much better! Much more color. The Toshiba is a smaller, cheaper and older TV than the Sony that's connected into the other video output, but it looks much better. So, of course, I wanted to do the same with the Sony." created="Sat, 01 Nov 2008 18:46:10 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I tried connecting the HDMI output to the Sony, but the picture looked terrible. I don't know how to describe it, but the colors were all washed out, text was blurry. I might try to take a picture so y'all can see what the deal is." created="Sat, 01 Nov 2008 18:48:26 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I tried hooking up a Mac Mini in the living room to the Samsung TV via HDMI, and got the same lousy picture. " created="Sat, 01 Nov 2008 18:49:40 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I unhooked the Mac Mini and connected my MacBook Pro to the Samsung, and got the same lousy picture. " created="Sat, 01 Nov 2008 18:50:22 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I've fiddled with the Displays section of the Preferences in every way I could and it makes no difference. I've turned everything off and on, still no difference. " created="Sat, 01 Nov 2008 18:50:41 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I can get more data. I might try to take a picture of the crummy image to post. " created="Sat, 01 Nov 2008 18:51:18 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Any advice would be much appreciated." created="Sat, 01 Nov 2008 18:51:43 GMT"/>
					<outline text="PS: I'm using &lt;a href=&quot;http://flickr.com/photos/scriptingnews/2992512130/&quot;&gt;Belkin DVI to HDMI&lt;/a&gt; adapters." created="Sat, 01 Nov 2008 19:28:08 GMT"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
